
   The UNIX command invokes the default shell.

   To invoke UNIX use one of the following options:

      - Command menu - Select UNIX + RETURN

      - COMMAND LINE - Type unix + RETURN

   Your  screen  will be cleared and the "UNIX:" prompt  
   will be displayed.

   To return to FACE from the shell, hold down the control
   key (CTRL) and press d, or type "exit" and press RETURN.
   You will then be prompted to press RETURN to continue.
